sql:
SELECT AVG(last_sold_price) AS average_price, county_id
FROM property_values
GROUP BY county_id;

external_knowledge:
- 'Sea of property listings' metaphorically represents the comprehensive data available in the database;
- 'Pluck a single pearl' symbolizes the selection of one specific property from the vast set of data;
- 'Complete profile of a property' includes all relevant details from the property, such as its address, type, financial history, and the economic context of its location;
- 'Diversity of property types' refers to the categorization of properties into residential and commercial;
- 'Average price of its siblings' refers to the calculation of the average last sold price across all properties.
